formdata:
**Below is a comprehensive list of available commands for <@1124185545350860811>.**

`?help`:** This command displays a helpful message or a list of available commands for users to understand the functionality and usage of the bot.**
*Usage: `?help`*
**Allowed Staff:** `All`

`?kick`: **This command allows administrators or users with appropriate permissions to remove or kick a member from the server. It is commonly used to enforce rules or remove disruptive individuals.**
*Usage: `?kick <@member>`*
**Allowed Staff:** <@&1114170198908481576>

`?ban`: **With this command, administrators can ban or permanently remove a member from the server. It is usually employed when a member repeatedly violates server rules or engages in severe misconduct.**
*Usage: `?ban <@member>`*
**Allowed Staff: **<@&1124655559606534157>, <@&1123603204408623257>

`?unban`:** This command allows administrators to reverse a ban on a member and grant them access back to the server. It is used when a member's ban is considered no longer necessary or if they have learned from their previous actions.**
*Usage: `?unban <@member>`*
**Allowed Staff:** <@&1124655559606534157>, <@&1123603204408623257>

`?mute`: **This command enables administrators to mute a member, preventing them from sending messages or participating in voice channels. Muting is often utilized to temporarily silence a member who is causing disturbances or engaging in inappropriate behavior.**
*Usage: `?mute <@member>`*
**Allowed Staff:** <@&1124655559606534157>, <@&1123603204408623257>, <@&1123603998407139468>

`?unmute`:** This command is used by administrators to remove the mute status from a previously muted member. It allows the member to regain their ability to send messages and participate in voice channels.**
*Usage: `?unmute <@member>`*
**Allowed Staff:**<@&1124655559606534157>, <@&1123603204408623257>, <@&1123603998407139468>

`?purge`:** With this command, administrators can delete a specified number of messages from a text channel. It is commonly employed to clean up chat logs or remove a large number of unwanted messages.**
*Usage: `?purge <number_of_messages>`*
**Allowed Staff:** <@&1114170198908481576>

`?trial`: **This command assigns the "<@&1123608011378798734>" role to the tagged user, initiating a trial period in the server. The purpose of this command is to grant temporary permissions to assess the member's suitability for a specific role or responsibility, such as moderating the server. During the trial period, the member can exercise the permissions associated with the Trial Moderator role. After the trial period ends, further evaluation or decision-making regarding the member's role may take place based on their performance.**
*Usage: `?trial <@member>`*
**Allowed Staff:**<@&1124655559606534157>, <@&1123603204408623257>

`?warn`: **Administrators use this command to issue a warning to a member who has violated server rules or engaged in undesirable behavior. Warnings are often accompanied by an explanation and serve as a formal notification to the member about their actions.**
*Usage: `?warn <@member> <reason>`*
Allowed Staff: <@&1114170198908481576>

`?bomb`: **This command typically deletes the channel in which command is used and creates a duplicate channel. Only use in case of raid.**
*Usage: `?bomb`*
**Allowed Staff:**<@&1124655559606534157>, <@&1123603204408623257>

`?smpart`:** This command adds the "<@&1125044693789573183>" role to the tagged user, designating them as a small partner. It is typically used to recognize and reward smaller partnered entities or individuals in the server.**
*Usage: `?smpart <@member>`*
**Allowed Staff:** <@&1123961550877765702>

`?bgpart`: **This command adds the "<@&1125044994890276884>" role to the tagged user, designating them as a big partner. It is typically used to recognize and reward larger partnered entities or individuals in the server.**
*Usage: `?bgpart <@member>`*
**Allowed Staff:** <@&1123961550877765702>
